      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat and add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced red onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the <strong>berbere seasoning </strong>and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>(save the rest for later!) with the <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span> </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomato has begun to soften</p>",
      "order": 5,
