    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, return the <strong>browned chicken breast portions </strong>to the pan with a couple of splashes of <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for a further 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked, stir through the <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until piping hot – this is your <strong>East African-style chicken pilaf</strong></p>",
